inn1.comm: immediate signs of swing as this bends towards first slip. Watson crunches a defensive drive
ooh, more swing for Anderson and a fuller length, too. Squeezed down to Bresnan at third man; opened the face nicely
excellent, swinging delivery on the off stump but Paine's behind it, driving to mid-off
attempts the booming outswinger but slides it down the leg side for the first wide of the day
off the back foot and guided to third man. Played that well, very late
left alone outside off, 86mph from Anderson. That one went straight
Watson is forward, defending solidly to end a tight first over
good start, bending this back in late on Paine who's struck high on the thigh

cracking delivery! Beauty from Sidebottom again moving back on Paine very late, cutting him in half and hitting him very high on the pad. Only half a shout from Prior and co. but that was spot on from the hairy winner
angled across him this time. He ignores it
that too is a little bit too wide. No swing for the second ball in a row
well that's a pretty good leave. Middle-and-off line, cuts and swings back on Paine who shoulders arms, leaving it alone on length
walks across to the off side to flick him to fine leg. Wright cleans up
too straight, worked to leg. The Big Bopper does the fielding
very good delivery moving back on Watson's off stump, but he's up to the challenge and defends with ferocity on the front foot. Nice, crunching sound as bat meets ball
steps forward and defends to point, opening the face at the last minute
has he edged that? No, well - I'm sure I heard something. Outside off, and with a horribly angled bat he tried to work it wide of the slips. Dangerous stroke indeed
the big inswinger raps him in front and Anderson implores Gould to raise his finger. Superb delivery, but perhaps sliding down
shot. Fabulous cover drive rockets to the fence. Everything was perfect: high front elbow, placement good and the timing was a thing of veritable beauty
bends sharply back onto him and he gets a thick inside edge onto his pad, a single scampered. But excellent lines from Sidebottom
that's sharp. Left alone outside off and Prior takes it in front of his face
ooh driven uppishly - Anderson pulls out a superb diving stop to his left at mid-off! He really is absurdly athletic for a fast bowler
defended out to the off side and after a stutter they're going for a run. Collingwood skips round from backward point and kicks the ball, but missed - and that would've been seriously tight!
defended on the back foot
and it's left alone outside off to end another naggingly good over
very solidly defended on the front foot
firmly slapped! Neat stroke to a rubbish long-hop, cut hard past Collingwood...who made a lousy effort to stop it. Perhaps his spikes got caught in the turf
again short of a length and left alone
that's a good nut bending back on the right-hander. He's right behind it
wide of the crease and defended on the back foot to the leg side. Bopara's alive and prevents the single
a KPish flick, on one leg, down to fine leg - super shot
on the back foot and powerfully defended to point
just outside off. Watson comes forward into a crunchingly solid forward defensive
goes back and tries to cut, but it's too close to him - too full, perhaps, too.
defended on the back foot to leg
excellent length - Watson on the back foot, defending to cover
blocked on the back foot out to the off side
jeepers, he's nailed that. Spanked to mid-off; Watson smiles, annoyed that he picked out the man so precisely
cuts and misses - bat hits the ground, I think, hence Anderson's half appeal. No, bat his pad
good delivery angling into him and he defends off the back foot to cover
powerfully flicked behind square but Bopara does really well on the boundary, making good yardage to cut it off. Surprisingly powerful throw, too, from the Big Bopper
a fine shot off the back foot, high front elbow, aided by two hilariously hapless misfields by firstly Collingwood, who couldn't reach it, then Morgan who was wrong-footed
watch out, cow corner, here it comes! Or not, as the case may be. An ugly cross-batted flap finds midwicket

massive wide down the leg side but Prior does brilliantly, diving to his left and palming it away. Interestingly, Prior's furious with himself for not taking it cleanly, which is a little harsh. That was a really good, diving effort
better line this time, swinging back from the off stump and forcing a defensive
outside off this time. Paine's leaving it alone
a touch fuller, and again outside off. Paine shoulders arms once more
and there it is! But it's too short. Again left alone by Paine on length alone, which is always a dangerous decision on English pitches. It brushes the very top of his pad

superb take from Prior whose wicketkeeping has improved out of all sight this summer. Paine attempts a KPish flamingo-flick, but it's off the pad and Prior dives athletically to his left and this time catches it in his left glove. Great effort
defended on the back foot
good start outside off. Defended on the back foot
ugly power - bosh! Too short, too straight, and Watson pulls it emphatically over midwicket
pushed out to the off side
excellent delivery angling in on Watson's off stump
only a touch too wide, but really it was the short length which allowed him to cut that
heroically driven to mid-off
good line, just outside off and threatening to move back on Watson who defends
firmly spanked to cover off the back foot
swings back on the off stump but he's more and more comfortable now, nudging it out to the off side. Bresnan swoops from mid-off but can't prevent the single
lovely Clarke-esque cover drive, though not quite timed sufficiently for four
shapes back. He defends
flicked off his hip for a couple
full, straight and defended. Nice length, from slightly wide on the crease
too much width this time and dabbed coolly behind point for a couple
right up to the blockhole again, and punched down to mid-off
nicked down to third man, a controlled edge
a good length again, no room to work the ball off the square, so solidly defended instead
clipped to midwicket and that's another tidy over
worked into space, and through they trot
something of a false stroke as Sidebottom bends the ball back into Paine and finds a thick inside-edge to square leg. Effective enough though
more of an effort ball, that climbed into Watson's gloves from nothing more dramatic than a good length. Brett Lee will be encouraged, especially after that pudding of a pitch at The Oval
hurried again, and defended into the crease. Tight, probing stuff from Sidebottom
I spoke too soon, a horrid wide long-hop from Sidebottom this time (well, relatively speaking) and Watson lashed it in front of point
full and wide, and awkwardly driven back to a sprawling bowler. A mostly tidy over
a swing and a miss outside off. Probing line
driven firmly, but straight to cover
had to hurry, as Swann swooped from backward square, but his throw was wayward
Bresnan's causing problems with his angled approach, spearing the ball in from wide on the crease. If he can nip one away, he'll be in business
tapped down to third man
another chaotic mix-up, Paine fell over as he pushed off for a single to gully, but Collingwood's shy was hopeless. Village all round
full and straight, poked back down the ground, and Wright nabs it in his followthrough
pushed to cover
driven firmly to mid-off, and they scamper through
an inside-out squirt through midwicket, and a bit sloppy in the field as well
Wright's excited as he goes up for an appeal, but that was going down leg
full length, looked like a variation ball from the back of the hand, and well directed too. But defended
full and straight again
good delivery, takes the inside-edge as Paine plays slightly down the wrong line
tucked off the hip to deep mid-on
Paine gives Bresnan the charge, but he sees him coming and bangs it in short. Good response, and the shot squirts aerially through cover

here's the breakthrough, and you have to say that was coming. Full again, a big mow from Watson, and Wright at short cover has a catch for the cameras as he goes airborne to take a comfortable two-handed pluck.
full and straight again, and that's an excellent over
Wright hustles in, and that's full length and on the pads, can't quite work it away
tucked to midwicket
tapped to point
and he's off the mark with a tuck round the corner
angled bat, into the gully

and that's the second wicket! More frustration from Australia, a touch short but Paine got completely underneath an attempted flick, and scooped a steepler to Eoin Morgan on the deep midwicket fence. A well-judged take, and England are in business
worked into the off-side
left alone outside off stump
bashed in a bit short, and through to the keeper as Clarke flinches out of the way
a great follow-up, straightening from a good length and Clarke played inside the line
on the pads, a bit loose to a man on 0, and Clarke is now a man on 1
drawn forward and defended. Tidy stuff from Bresnan
worked out to midwicket with a roll of the wrists
a fat edge, not entirely planned, but utterly effective. Third man can't cut that off
full again, and blocked back down the track
clipped into the leg-side again
no rush to get the runs ticking again. Worked off the hip to no avail
full and straight, and driven calmly to mid-on
pushed into the covers
dabbed past point and a rare single
driven back down the ground but with no great timing
punched firmly off the back foot, but Morgan pounces well in the covers to save the boundary
a hint of width and slashed hard, but straight to point
stands tall to punch off the back foot again, and Strauss at short cover was nearly in business. A very tidy over
bouncer, and Clarke is utterly nailed by that one. A loose swish of the blade, a thin edge, and an easy catch for Prior. Excellent change of approach from Wright, and he's made a vital breakthrough
short again, and excellent aggression. Ferguson doesn't pick that at all, and wears the ball as it thuds off his ribs
fuller and straighter, and defended this time
speared in again. Defended with leaden feet
tucked square
short again, and a warm round of applause for a spirited and successful over
good leave outside off
good line on off stump - well defended, mind
full of length, drawing him into a defensive drive
very wide and he cuts it hard to third man
good, straight ball turned to leg
woops! Miles down the leg side
good thinking, an inswinging and attempted yorker, but it's crisply dug out and they scamper for two
good length and it's blocked firmly off the back foot
crunching pull in front of square
neatly punched, high front elbow, just behind square on the off side
very good line again, and it's defended solidly off the back foot
again, another excellent delivery just short of a length and a touch straighter. Right behind it
too straight this time, though, and White comfortably picks him off for a single to mid-on
gorgeous shot! Just for two, but creamily driven out to deep extra cover
wider of the crease and zeroing in on his off stump. Cautiously defended
more aggressively  driven, this time to short extra
fullish from Anderson, White blocks to leg
outside off and stroked to deep extra cover
ooh good delivery but well played. An attempted yorker, dug out for a single to mid-on, though his digging was done "on the walk," which is always fraught with danger
punched out to the off side
could've played that on the front foot. Patted back to the bowler
driven inside out to mid-off, and a touch uppishly
got onto that pull really, really quickly. Just didn't get up enough to trouble him and it was hooked, rather than pulled, behind square for four
on middle stump and firmly defended
down the leg side by quite some distance
again too straight - Wright's tiring a bit here - and nudged to square leg
crunch! Sheesh, he really gave that some hammer on the back foot - slapping it to deep extra cover
bouncer, ignored
good line outside off and it's forced off the back foot to third man. Not entirely convincingly
timing was spot on, driving straight down the ground and nutmegging Anderson. Class. Driven on the up, too
defended to point
even better! Driven on the up out through extra cover. Serious shot, and the hundred's up for Australia
that too is driven down the ground, though it didn't appear he timed it perfectly. Bat twisted in his hands and it missed the non-striker's stumps by no more than an inch
outside edge to third man
prods a defensive
good from Wright, very straight and it kept a touch low, too
a very solid forward defence from White
neat flick off his legs and short midwicket makes a total and utter meal of it
very straight, very defended
60mph. 60mph. That's Monty's slower-ball speed, that. White flips him to leg
floaty little number outside off, driven out to the off side
another off cutter which is defended. Accurate stuff from Collingwood
60.8mph, very floaty, and he can't make anything of it. Patted back to the bowler
forced off the back foot: brilliantly stopped by the bowler in his follow-through. Nice first over, that
outside off, patted back to Swann
outside off and turned to mid-on off the back foot
sweetly played, stepping forward before flicking it from off stump behind square on the leg side
ah, well bowled - tossed that up higher, and White went for a fat flick to leg but couldn't get hold of it
White lunges forward a little ungainly, blocking to leg
down the pitch flicking to leg
nurdled to the leg side
fantastic shot, his best of the day. Placed it so well - big front stride and drove it powerfully through extra cover
fuller and he works it to leg
squared up by a fine delivery on the off stump. Another off-cutter and he was too early on it
flicked to leg
worked to leg once more to end another tight over
tossed up outside the off stump and he comes forward to flick it to leg
shorter delivery and he skips down the pitch but can't make anything of it
marvellous shot - remarkable power from White. Firm, crunching sweep for four
neat little nurdle to leg and they take a tight single. Collingwood fumbled at short midwicket
flatter and it's a bit too straight, nurdled around the corner for another cheeky single
worked to long-on on the walk
on the pads, clipped to midwicket
outside off, and drilled firmly into the covers, but no great power in the stroke
driven, but through the shot a fraction early. That loops over Collingwood and safely down to mid-off
Collingwood nutmegs himself in his followthrough, which is rare. The batsmen steal a single
whipped to midwicket
tapped back to the bowler, who this time fields it well. And finds the humour in it as well
down the track, and driven airily into space at long-off
the crowd gets excited as Swann finds some spin and bounce, but there's no bat involved as Prior takes the catch
an ugly swipe to leg, and it gets its rewards. Nothing
turned square. The shot, not the ball, that is
a measured prod down to long-off. Steady is the euphemistic word I'd use for this
turned round the corner. Four singles in the over
clipped off the pads
a touch shorter but straight. Nudged urgently to cover
nice shot, makes room with good footwork, and a well-placed loft over the cover fielder
stretches forward, and tucked to midwicket
on the pads, tucked into space
twirled into the blockhole, and duly blocked down the ground, into the gap
Got 'im! First ball, outside off, a decent line and length, and White is drawn into an attempted glide to third man. But his edge is just too thin, and Prior gathers well behind the stumps
off the mark first-ball
a touch short, and worked off the hip to backward square
on the pads, tucked to square leg
nurdle schmurdle, down to deep midwicket
a open-faced glide to deep cover
on the pads
threatens to straighten, and pushed to backward point
another nudge into the gap. He's good at that
dragged forward from round the wicket, and not much danger of that lbw appeal being upheld
and Hussey hands the strike back again
forward and defended, solidly this time
tapped to third man
straight, and hurried into a defensive push
outside off, and edged into the gully
tries to work the angles, but that's good wicket-to-wicket bowling
driven firmly down to long-off, and they thought about two, but not for long
a wristy manoeuvre into the leg-side. Promising spell from Bopara
floated up from round the wicket, chiselled into the leg-side
a wristy drive to midwicket
fully forward and sniffs the leather on a defensive block
finds the gap at midwicket
tip-and-run, into the covers
bowled him! Fine ball but average shot. Hussey's off stump has been a target all summer, and that one just tweaked enough to peg it back. He was playing all down the wrong line there
driven hard to point
worked firmly out to deep midwicket
drawn forward again, and defended to cover
width, and a measured steer to deep point
clipped just wide of a diving short midwicket, and another single to the tally
Australia are content to deal in singles - this one dribbles down to long-on
big stride and pushed to point
shouts of catch it, but no-one is there to cut it off as it loops up at silly point
a hefty slog-sweep and nicely placed, just to the left of the diving Anderson at square leg, and to the right of Shah the boundary sweeper
more oohs, but no real drama
works the gap again.
a stride down the pitch and an ambitious swish around the front pad finds space at fine leg
outside off, and beats a loose waft. Good start
bashed back to the bowler, who fields in his followthrough
clipped down to mid-on
calmly driven to long-off
bustled onto a middle-and-leg line, and clipped away
great finish to the over. Good carry outside off, and that zips through to the keeper
defended to the leg side
swept powerfully, monstrously, but straight through Anderson at square-leg - not sure how he managed to muck that one up
skips down the pitch and flicks hard to midwicket
good comeback from Swann, quicker ball hurries him into a defensive, and what a defensive it was
short of a length, straight, and it's nudged to leg but without any power or intent
another nudge to leg, good tight bowling from Swann
boink. Steps to leg, tries to flap it over cover but misses completely
oh bowled! Superb leg-cutter which really bounced on Ferguson who was beaten comprehensively. He's sharp, Wright
cuts back on him and he forces it hard, but straight to short extra
short of a length and that's pulled square for four, got on top of that. We've seen quite a bit of irregular bounce today. Some have climbed, others haven't
aggressively slashed to third man, stepping outside leg and flaying it safely down to that region
well bowled. Good attempted yorker dug out to deep square leg
and after a long delay, Gould raises his finger. Quicker ball, he went for a sweep but was trapped dead in front of middle
blocked on the front foot
tickled around the corner to Anderson who wings in a throw to Swann, but it's a terrible one which scuds through low and Swann can't retrieve it
nudged to leg
tossed up on middle and Johnson defends to leg for a single
crisp clip (try saying that with a wet moustache) to mid-on
that's not his fifty. Another sharp delivery - too quick for Ferguson who went for a pull but was hit in the midriff, or thereabouts

crashing shot by Johnson. When he times it, they fairly fly. Square of the wicket, and Morgan races around the boundary and might have done brilliantly to save four there. Full-length dive and after three replays it's confirmed he's done quite marvellously
fifty for Ferguson! Top knock from a very impressive young player. Strong hook for four brings up his half-century
steps down the pitch and cracks this full toss but straight to deep cover point
nailed it! Pulled in front of square. That reverberated around Lord's with the crispest of cracks
lines up another heave across the line but can't time it, bit too full
full toss boshed to mid-on, who is deep
nice and full, Johnson clunks it down the ground to bring up Australia's 200
steps outside leg but Anderson sees him and fires it in at his legs. Times it nicely back to Anderson who makes a good stop
down the leg side
too straight for that leg-side flip! Anderson fires it in straight; Ferguson tries to whack him over the leg side and is cleaned up
bouncer! Woo! That was sharp and Lee snapped his head out of the way at the last moment. That's got him hopping
fast inswinger but a bit wide
serious shot, that. Nothing more than a flip, or pick-up off his legs, but he's timed it brilliantly in front of square
bang. Lifted over the infield to long-on. Johnson's setup is ridiculously simple: see ball, hit ball. Bats like a golfer in many ways
very full and clipped hard around the corner
smashed to Shah at extra cover who didn't need to move. No more need be said
dug out square of the wicket
squeezes this full toss out to extra cover but just for a single
punched to point
shorter ball and he tries to uppercut it with Gilchristian flare, but realises he's not  up to his class
super fielding off his own bowling as Hauritz nails a drive to Anderson's left
down the leg side
four byes! An attempted yorker misses a) the leg stump b) Hauritz's flashing blade and c) Prior's left glove
blocked off the back foot to mid-off for a quick single
very full and carved only for a strike-stealing single to long-off
angled into his legs, forced out to the off side but only for a single
very wide and he squeezes it out to deep backward point. And they get two! Collingwood's having a mild shocker in the field today by his lofty standards
wellied for a single to leg. Hauritz shakes his head in disgust
slides this down the leg side. He's over the wicket to the left-hander, and batsman and bowler both chuckle that it wasn't called a wide.
savagely driven to extra cover! Stepped outside leg and creamed it, but couldn't quite break through the packed off side
down the leg side and he gets a thick inside edge

worked off his hip for a couple to deep square leg. Excellent work by Bopara who dives, then flips the ball up to Sidebottom who wings in a throw. The Lord's crowd, most of whom are fast asleep, briefly rise from their Sunday slumber and put their hands together
forced out to the off side
fantastic shot! Deft brilliance from Johnson, scooping it very fine for four. Made it into a full toss and flipped it around the corner from outside off. Superb
miles outside off
oh that's just obscene from Johnson! Another scorching pick-up from outside off, hurtling it through midwicket for four
low full toss clunked to long-off. Good hustling yields two
swipes and misses outside off, and Johnson drops an f-bomb in frustration
nice stroke for a single, lofting it short of long-off
down the leg side, Johnson is yorked but gets an inside edge which evades the diving Prior. Sidebottom is furious as ever, his tonnage of hair flapping all over the place in disgust
well bowled, very full and it hits him on the pads, though they steal another single just to spite poor old SIdebottom
short of a length, much slower, and they nick another single as Hauritz drops it to leg
great cricket! A reverse-scoop, quite brilliant really, which flies over short third man. Excellent thinking from Johnson
another big swing but can't quite time it, and Johnson's clearly a bit peeved that Australia couldn't get to 250

inn2.comm: on the hips and tucked square for a settling single
good bail-rattling line and length,  but comfortably negotiated by Bopara
that's a snorter, angled into Bopara, nipped away up the hill, and sizzled past the edge. He's going to be a handful today, I sense
wider this time, and a more confident leave
banged in short, and that should have been a wide. But he gets away with one
outside off, no risk of a stroke. A tidy start
curled onto a good length
dabbed to point
outside off, no great pace or movement, but a tidy enough line
short and wide, and that's a gift. Strauss cuts so well he ought to be a director
on the hips, worked to midwicket to rotate the strike
full and straight. Defended with a perpendicular bat
right up in the blockhole, but just outside off stump. Pushed away
nice line, even better leave. The ball hops obediently over off stump
full again, but arrow straight. Defended
tidy line and length again. Got a good rhythm going already
bit of extra lift, deflected to midwicket
great line and length, climbing as the ball reaches the middle of Bopara's bat. Defended with a loud "no!"
lucky for Strauss! A loose drive with little foot movement, and he chops the ball onto his pads but the ricochet misses the stumps
poor ball, pushed across the left-hander towards third man, and helped on its way
solid defence, despite a trigger movement that implied he was about to clobber the ball
driven into the covers
slower ball, and it was timely as well, as Strauss was advancing
another slower ball, Strauss waits and guides a single to third man. Inventive over
turned to square leg. Strauss has a lot of time for his shots, even against 90mph bowlers
less time on that occasion! Defended with a hop onto the back foot
short, and pulled, and that was in the air for longer than he might have liked. A bit of a top-edge meant Bracken at backward square was interested, but it landed safe
eight dot balls and counting for Ravi, as that one is prodded into the off side
short, too short. Bopara flinched as it went by, but it was well out of his range
drawn forward and defended on off stump
Bopara's off the mark, but how close was that! A flashy inside-edge, that misses leg stump by the membrane of a strand of DNA. They all count
good start, full and straight
up to the blockhole again, and defended
a touch shorter, a bit of width, and worked uppishly to deep point. Decent stroke, and his first unflukey runs
full again, pushed calmly to midwicket
drilled into the covers off the back foot
too straight this time, and that is sweetly timed through midwicket. Such a narrow margin when Strauss is in this form
short, and that's a very unconvincing attempted pull. Almost too lackadaisical, and that zips through to the keeper
slower ball, and it swings as well. Bopara sees it well enough, and feels a drive back to the bowler
that's more like it from Bopara, a crunched back-foot drive that doesn't quite have the legs to go to the rope, but the placement is impeccable
whoops, that's an overstep, so here comes a free hit
Strauss backs away and wellies a smeared drive into the covers
firmly pushed into the covers. Well fielded, but signs of improved timing for Bopara
worked off the pads, another single, and Strauss is looking good
too much width, but for once Strauss misses out. Even Stanley Kubrick had some duff cuts
dabbed to backward point and Bopara has to scamper. But scamper he does
a wristy cut-cum-drive to backward point, but Clarke intercepts well
tucked off the stumps, using Johnson's angles to do the work for him
slower ball, and Bopara is foxed. Outside off though, so no damage done
another slower ball, but straighter this time, and Bopara defends
plays across the line, and nearly chips a leading edge into the covers. He's slower than he looks, evidently
pushed into the leg side
defended to short cover
Bopara advances but can't get his shot away. And that shot prompts Paine to don his lid and come up to the stumps
worked out to point by the newly crease-bound Bopara
a loose swish, but he gets enough bat on the shot to squeeze one out to midwicket
too much width and that is slashed away imperiously. Half a cut, half a square drive. All runs
short but straight, and nurdled to midwicket
on the pads, turned to square leg
driven out to point, and Clarke flings a shy at the non-striker's end, just for good measure
more strike rotation, but England are looking composed now
full and straight, chipped to midwicket
goes for a pull down the leg side but misses
wide of the off stump, this time. Not called, though, much to Strauss's annoyance
don't bowl there. That's just daft. Short, wide, cut, four.
pulled again but mistimed and slightly skewed, though it lands perfectly safely
this is poor from Hopes really. Down the leg side and Bopara helps it on its way with a flick of the wrists
a better, straighter ball is well defended this time
tucked to leg
outside off, by quite a distance, and Bopara goes for glory but nearly falls on his sword
squeezed out to point
runs down the pitch and check-drives to cover for an anguish-filled hasty single
little tickle off his legs and Strauss wants two to Lee, who has a seriously good arm, but not this time! That's a shocking throw from Lee, straight at the middle of the pitch
another neat nurdle for a nourishing single
mmmmonstrous shot! A highly effective slog-sweep of great power and placement
see, one-day cricket doesn't need to be bish, bash, bosh the whole time. A delicate dab, opening the face, brings Strauss four. Unless he edged it. Erm, well, a bit of both there
just outside off and guided to point
a rank long-hop is smashed through midwicket on the back foot. Imperious stuff from Strauss
better line but again too short. Defended to point
again too short but nicely turned with a flick of the wrists
defended to leg and Paine is quick to the ball to prevent Bopara's rather impetuous thought of stealing a single
on his legs and tickled for a single
steps to the off side before flicking him to leg
turned to leg
down the pitch and drives to deepish mid-on
good work by Paine to cut off the single, scampering to his right
much better line by Hauritz to end the over, on the off stump and attacking the stumps
good start outside off and defended
well! Down the pitch, tries to smack him over the top but gets a bottom edge. "Spin! Spin" shouts Strauss to Bopara who hasn't a clue where the ball's gone, and it backspins just past his stumps
elegantly driven to mid-on
again he comes dancing down the pitch like a veritable cat on an averagely warm tin roof, smudging the ball to mid-on
he's got him and Watson's over the moon! Bopara walked across his stumps and tried to work it through midwicket but that's taking out middle-and-leg
defended on the back foot to end a wicket maiden by Watson. Superb start from him
Strauss flicks him to leg
a more purposeful nudge to leg for a single
beaten by the arm ball! Good take by Paine. That hurried through on Prior
again that raced through to Prior but he read it better this time, defending it to leg to get off the mark
biggish shout for lbw but that's sliding down
the calmest of defensives
well wide and well full, too. Prior can't make contact with this cut-cum-slice-cum-drive
terrible shot by Prior. A loose flap outside off, on the up, and he gets a thin edge through to Paine
defended solidly back to the bowler

good line outside off and chopped to the off side by Shah, who thought he wanted a single, ran a little way down the pitch, then shouted no to Strauss. Who was never running anywhere. So he was probably shouting no to himself
full toss sliced behind square. Third man (Johnson) does really well. Rocket arm.
chopped to the off side
